<para id="eip-945"><emphasis effect="bold">Two Column Step by Step Example of a Sampling Distribution for a Mean</emphasis></para><para id="import-auto-id1164902426184">A study involving stress is done on a college campus among the students. The stress scores follow a uniform distribution with the lowest stress score equal to 1 and the highest equal to 5. </para>
        <para id="import-auto-id1164901622165">Using a random sample of 50 students, find the probability that the mean stress score for the 50 students is less than 2.65.</para><table xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" id="import-auto-id1164905511022" summary="This is a table with 2 columns and 6 rows. The first column is an outline of what tasks need to be done to create a sampling distribution for a mean. The second column is a step by step solution to the problem listed above this table.">
